<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3472380>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Growth line traces of Turritellidae species based on own data; bold: type species of genera; black: Paratethyan species; asterisk: non-Paratethyan species (unknown basal sinuses are left blank)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3472380/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3472419>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. A–D. Allmonia paucicincta (Sacco, 1895), Burgschleinitz (Austria). A. Holotype, NHMW 1846/0010/0014. B1–B3. Collection Anton Breitenberger. C. NHMW 2018/0128/0002. D. NHMW 2018/0128/000. E. Turritella (Protoma) telleri Hilber, 1993, holotype, Ivanji dol (Slovenia), UMJG&P 1247. F–H. Allmonia cathedralis (Brongniart, 1823), Léognan (France). F1–F2. NHMW 1858/0018/0146. G. NHMW 1858/0018/0146. H. NHMW 1858/0018/0146. I–J. Allmonia funiculata (Borson, 1821), Torino Hills (Italy). I. NHMW 1862/0049/0026. J. NHMW 1854/0016/0209." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3472419/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3472370>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Paleogeography of the Paratethys during the early Miocene (Burdigalian, Eggenburgian, Sakaraulian) and the middle Miocene (Langhian, Badenian, Tarkhanian) (modified after Popov et al. 2004 and Neubauer et al. 2015)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3472370/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3472374>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Measurements for shell morphology and whorl profiles (adopted from Allmon 1996) (SL = shell length, MD = maximum diameter, AA = apical angle, PA = pleural angle)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3472374/files/figure.png" ;
